00:07:31,116 --> 00:07:31,556
Why Fractals?

139
00:07:31,556 --> 00:07:34,136
Our human brains are hardwired to find patterns.

140
00:07:34,136 --> 00:07:36,457
They help us cluster and predict the constant flow

141
00:07:36,457 --> 00:07:38,597
of information streaming into our brains,

142
00:07:38,597 --> 00:07:41,638
which lets us survive and act and optimize our performance

143
00:07:41,638 --> 00:07:42,898
in an otherwise overwhelming world.

144
00:07:42,898 --> 00:07:45,699
Now, some patterns are really easy to see.

145
00:07:45,699 --> 00:07:47,839
Songs have choruses versus bridges.

146
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:50,200
Novels have three-act structures, heroes journeys,

147
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,040
politics ebb and flow, conservative to liberal,

148
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:52,560
and back again.

149
00:07:54,509 --> 00:07:56,550
But games aren't simple nor linear entities.

150
00:07:56,550 --> 00:07:58,791
They're these really vast and complex systems,

151
00:07:58,791 --> 00:08:00,911
multifaceted and multilayered.

152
00:08:00,911 --> 00:08:02,872
Even games with the simplest underpinnings

153
00:08:02,872 --> 00:08:05,193
can have these vast and unpredictable results.

154
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:05,953
And that's the beauty of fractals too.

155
00:08:05,953 --> 00:08:10,294
Fractals are these patterns that exist across scale

156
00:08:10,294 --> 00:08:12,155
that describe infinite systems.

157
00:08:12,155 --> 00:08:15,196
The defining property of a fractal is that it is self-similar

158
00:08:15,196 --> 00:08:17,817
which means you can see the same basic shapes and patterns

159
00:08:17,817 --> 00:08:19,938
no matter how far you zoom in and out,

160
00:08:19,938 --> 00:08:22,438
in or out, and often when you translate your view as well.

161
00:08:24,044 --> 00:08:25,525
And all of that infinite complexity

162
00:08:25,525 --> 00:08:28,027
comes from one tiny little set of variables.

163
00:08:28,027 --> 00:08:29,228
All fractals have at their heart

164
00:08:29,228 --> 00:08:30,509
some sort of equation or algorithm

165
00:08:30,509 --> 00:08:32,290
that defines that repeating pattern.

166
00:08:32,290 --> 00:08:34,112
This one is for the Mandelbrot set.

167
00:08:34,112 --> 00:08:37,174
That single algorithm feeds back in on itself,

168
00:08:37,174 --> 00:08:41,017
multiplying outward, downward, upward.

169
00:08:41,017 --> 00:08:43,599
With just one underlying and foundational set of variables,

170
00:08:43,599 --> 00:08:46,762
an infinite and beautifully resonant pattern emerges.

171
00:08:46,762 --> 00:08:49,424
And ultimately, that's exactly what we want with our games.

172
00:08:49,424 --> 00:08:50,545
We want coherent design

173
00:08:50,545 --> 00:08:52,406
across massive interrelated systems.

174
00:08:53,538 --> 00:08:55,278
This means that your vision as a designer

175
00:08:55,278 --> 00:08:57,499
